            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Fairness and Accuracy in Reporting (FAIR) is a progressive media watch organization founded in 1986 by journalist Jeff Cohen. FAIR publishes 
                <title render="italic">Extra!</title>a magazine of media criticism and produces 
                <title render="italic">Counterspin</title>, a radio news program. It is active against censorship, advocates diversity, and the break up of the dominant media conglomerates. The collection includes: correspondence (mostly that of Jeff Cohen), internal documents, and back issues of publications.</abstract>
        </did>
        <custodhist id="ref4">
            <head>Provenance</head>
